WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   TEM
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   COLUMBUS, Ohio -- Temco National Corp. said it expects to
report a $1 million gain in its second quarter from the sale
of a wholesale medical supply unit to Foster Medical Supply
Inc.
   Terms of the sale weren't disclosed.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Foster, a closely held company based in Dedham, Mass.,
said the medical supply unit, owned by Temco's Wendt-Bristol
Co. subsidiary, will be combined with its current operations.
</TEXT>
