<HL>
   EMC Corp. to Report Profit
</HL>
<DATE>
04/17/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C13
</SO>
<CO>
   EMC
</CO>
<LP>
   HOPKINTON, Mass. -- EMC Corp. said it expects to report a
profit of about $735,000, or three cents to four cents a
share, on record revenue of about $40 million for the first
quarter.
   Last year, the maker of computer parts reported a net loss
of $7.5 million, or 32 cents a share, on revenue of $24.1
million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company said the growth reflects improved sales of its
disk systems and its so-called solid state disks, which use
semiconductors that work in place of disk drives.
</TEXT>
