<IN>
RESTAURANTS, FAST-FOOD, CATERING (RES)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- Marriott Corp. said it completed the sale of
its Roy Rogers restaurant business to Hardee's Food Systems
Inc. for $365 million in cash, plus the assumption by
Hardee's of certain liabilities. Hardees is a unit of Imasco
Ltd.
   The Roy Rogers chain consists of more than 600
restaurants, of which more than 350 are company owned.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Marriott said the sale would have no impact on 1990
earnings because proceeds are being invested in its remaining
family restaurant business.
