   Business Brief -- Universal Foods Corp.:
   Fiscal 2nd-Quarter Profit
   Rose 19% to $10 Million
</HL>
<DATE>
04/17/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   UFC
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Universal Foods Corp., citing the benefits of a continuing
push into what it calls "high growth, high return
businesses," said net income for its second quarter ended
March 31 climbed 19%.
   The Milwaukee-based food products concern reported
earnings of $10 million, or 40 cents a share, up from the
year-earlier $8.4 million, or an adjusted 34 cents a share.
Per-share earnings figures reflect an increase in shares
outstanding to 25.3 million from the year-earlier 24.9
million, which was adjusted for a 3-for-2 stock split paid
last October.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Revenue rose 8.9% to $219.7 million from $201.6 million.
   The company said it is "confident that our shareholders
will see a strong increase in earnings during fiscal 1990."
   For the fiscal first half, Universal's net increased 21%
to $23.4 million, or 93 cents a share, from $19.2 million, or
78 cents a share, a year earlier. Revenue rose 14% to $444.1
million from $389.3 million.
</TEXT>
