<HL>
   Business Brief -- Battery One-Stop Inc.:
   Group Led by DeBartolo
   Acquires 13.2% of Company
</HL>
<DATE>
04/17/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Edward J. DeBartolo said he and an investment group have
acquired 13.2% of Battery One-Stop Inc.
   The Canadian company issued the DeBartolo group 375,000
units, each unit consisting of one share of common stock and
a half warrant to purchase one share per full warrant. The
warrants are exercisable for two years, at a price of $5 a
share.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   As a result, the DeBartolo group holds 1.3 million common
shares of Battery One-Stop and warrants for an additional
187,500 shares, as well as additional rights. The DeBartolo
holdings represent 19.2% of Battery One-Stop's common stock
on a fully diluted basis and 13.2% percent on an undiluted
basis. The group plans to purchase another 375,000 common
shares of Battery One-Stop from its officers.
   The DeBartolo group said the purchase was made for
long-term investment. Battery One-Stop, a specialty kiosk
retailer of batteries and battery-powered electronic
products, said funds raised by the sale will be used to
continue expansion in the U.S.
</TEXT>
