   PHILADELPHIA -- Cedar Group Inc. said it entered an
agreement in principle to acquire Gardenbolt International
for $6 million in cash at closing, and an additional $1
million contingent upon Gardenbolt's future results over a
four-year period. Cedar Group distributes nuts, bolts and
related products. Gardenbolt, of Sayreville, N.J., imports
fasteners. The acquisition is subject to definitive
agreements and due diligence.
